{
  "name": "Water Release Water Severing Wave",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Water.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You cup your hands against your mouth releasing a torrent of highly pressurized water and using your chakra like a nozzle. You sweep your head from side to side targeting a cone area up to 600 feet in distance. Creatures caught in the radius of this jutsu must make a Dexterity saving throw, taking 8d10 cold damage on a failed save.</p><p>If used near a sufficient source of water, reduce the chakra cost of this jutsu by 2 or you can force affected creatures to make a constitution saving throw, gaining 2 ranks of chilled on a failed save.</p><p>At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above A-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and increase the damage by 1d10 for each damage type.</p>",
